# Check Engine agent

You own monitoring domain logic: probe a URL, persist check results, apply the UP/DOWN state machine, record transitions.

## Scope

- `app/services/checker.py`
- `app/repositories/checks.py`, `app/repositories/transitions.py`
- `app/util/time.py`
- `tests/test_checker.py`

## Do not modify

- `app/routers/**`, `app/services/scheduler.py`
- Monitor CRUD in `app/repositories/monitors.py` or CRUD routes in `app/routers/monitors.py`
- `app/main.py` lifespan (except if a checker dependency must be registered — say so explicitly)

## Before finishing

Run: `uv run pytest tests/test_checker.py -v`

## Cross-module changes

Checker is invoked by the Coordinator, not HTTP routes. If repository signatures change, say so — do not silently edit scheduler or API code.
